Vice President Biden's statement highlights the issue of violence against women globally. He emphasizes that such violence not only causes suffering but also hinders economic development, threatens peace and prosperity, and prevents full participation in civic life. He calls for better action to address this epidemic, mentioning instances like domestic violence, rape as a weapon of war, and attacks on girls going to school. The statement also mentions the commitment of the U.S. government to investing in women's health, education, and rights, and outlines efforts to reduce gender-based violence in schools, provide care for rape victims, and train health workers. The Vice President concludes by affirming the government's dedication to responding to, reducing, and ultimately eliminating gender-based violence worldwide.